<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Letter Book Copy: letters copied into a bound letter-book ]">LB</abbr> (recopied), <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-05-02-0180-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0180-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>David Kennedy was quartermaster of the 1st Virginia Regiment, and William Henry was brought to Winchester by St. Clair to repair the arms that Blair sent from Williamsburg.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-05-02-0180-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0180-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-05-02-0181" class="document">GW to Robert Rutherford, this date</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-05-02-0180-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-02-05-02-0180-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>On 17 June 1758 Bryan Bruin received from GW 5.10 for Rent of my House as Hospital for the Virga Troops. Certified by Jas Craik Surgeon. <img class="char" src="images/char-per-trans.png" alt="[per]"/> me Bry. Bruin (Va. Regimental Receipt Book, 1758, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>).</p>

</div>
